As a Trainer I encourage you NOT to walk into your first training session after Christmas with the mindset of ‚Äòburning off Christmas Day calories‚Äô.
Train because it makes you FEEL good. Train because you are grateful that you can move your body in such a way. Train because you‚Äôre disciplined and it‚Äôs part of your routine. Train because it gives you confidence. Train because you‚Äôve got fitness goals to reach in 2020. Train because you LOVE it! üí™üèº

We are social beings and 9.9/10 times we associate coming together and celebrating with food. Christmas Day is no exception. As a Nutritionist, my biggest piece of advice over this festive period is to find BALANCE.
Go back for seconds but also listen to your hunger and full cues (try not to go too far past the full ones üòâ). Indulge yourself in sweets and desserts but don‚Äôt forget to have some greens at some point too. If you‚Äôre having a few drinks, make sure you‚Äôve had or are having some water. This is balance.
Am I going to eat too much on Christmas Day? Yes. 
Am I going to eat foods that aren‚Äôt typically seen in my everyday diet? Yes.
Am I going to feel guilty about it? No.
It is ONE day. One day of eating a little (or a lot) more than normal and it isn‚Äôt going to completely derail your health and fitness journey. 
Enjoy yourself and soak in the day making memories with your family and friends üéÑ

SWIPE ‚û°Ô∏è This is one of my FAVOURITE workouts! I program this for my @theground_australia Family twice a year - every Christmas and in July (Christmas in July üòâ)! Anddd this year, I‚Äôm sharing it with you all! Although I keep it the same so that my clients can retest themselves every 6 months to evaluate their progress, the great thing about this workout is that you can create it using ANY exercises you like.

12 DAYS OF CHRISTMAS üéÑ
Here‚Äôs the workout reps and exercises: 
1 Sumo Deadlift High Pull (25kg)
2 Thrusters (25kg)
3 Push Press (25kg)
4 Power Cleans (25kg)
5 Power Snatches (25kg)
6 Kettlbell Swings (16kg)
7 Pull Ups
8 Knees To Elbows
9 Box Jumps (20‚Äù)
10 Double Unders
11 Burpees
12 Plate Overhead Alt. Lunges (10kg)

Now for the IMPORTANT part! How the workout is performed (think of the 12 Days of Christmas song):
1 SDHP, 1 SDHP + 2 Thrusters, 1 SDHP + 2 Thrusters + 3 Push Press, 1 SDHP + 2 Thrusters + 3 Push Press + 4 Power Cleans, 1 SDHP + 2 Thrusters + 3 Push Press + 4 Power Cleans + 5 Power Snatches... and so on.
Basically you begin each round at the start of the exercises and add one more exercise each round until you complete a full round that includes the Plate Overhead Alt. Lunges.
üí™üèº Let me know if you give this workout a go!!

I have always been able to run, but I haven‚Äôt always been strong.
It wasn‚Äôt luck, luck has nothing to do with it. Because luck won‚Äôt get you out of bed in the morning. Luck won‚Äôt set your goals. Luck won‚Äôt push you for that extra rep.
It really comes down to a combination of two things: hard work and consistency... the recipe to success in ANYTHING.
Get ready to make sacrifices, to be disciplined, to find inner strengths you never knew you had, and to get out of your comfort zone and get comfortable with the uncomfortable.
It‚Äôs not going to be easy, but the feeling of being able to say "wow, I couldn't do that last week" will be worth EVERY single bit of it.
Coming from someone who walked into a Crossfit box years ago and struggled to do push ups on her knees, dreaming about how amazing it would be to be able to do just one pull up, let me tell you... if I can do it, YOU can do it too!

Up until now my training hasn‚Äôt had a whole lot of structure. I‚Äôve really just been gauging where I‚Äôm at post-pregnancy, what skills my body can and can‚Äôt do anymore, and what my new 1RM‚Äôs are. 
So this weekend I‚Äôm setting aside some time to write myself a training program. It‚Äôs time to start TRAINING with PURPOSE and progressively overloading these muscles so I can start ticking off some of the postpartum goals I set for myself üí™üèº I‚Äôm not waiting until the new year, I‚Äôm starting my program NOW!
If there‚Äôs something you are wanting to start, do it NOW! Don‚Äôt put it off until 2020 because there‚Äôs so much you can achieve and so much progress you can make in these next 4 weeks!

28 min EMOM:
4 rounds - 7 exercises
1. 12 Push Ups
2. 9 Elevated Ring Rows
3. 3 Power Cleans @ 80% max
4. 100m Sprint
5. 18 American KB Swings
6. 24 Squat Jumps
7. 40sec Handstand Hold (wall assisted)

PS. Look the expansion at @theground_australia is nearly done!! üòç

Training impacts so much more than your body‚Äôs physical ability to do something. It is more than the physical changes you see in the mirror. More than the way your body looks.

For me, I don‚Äôt think that it‚Äôs a coincidence that my confidence grew as my strength grew. It‚Äôs not a coincidence that the mental strength, determination and drive I have gained, reflects in all areas of my life. Or that I‚Äôm happiest when I‚Äôm able to train consistently.

I‚Äôd love to know your story. What‚Äôs one thing that training or exercise has done for you beyond the physical aspects?

IT‚ÄôS GO TIME!!
18 months + 5 days after opening and we are tearing down our big Ground wall!! It is so bittersweet because I love this wall. To me, having our name up there represents the blood, sweat and tears that Jake and I put into this place. If you have been following my journey from when we opened @theground_australia, you will remember us giving ourselves the ridiculously short timeframe of opening in 4 weeks after getting the keys, the back to back 5:00am - 8:00pm working days for months at the beginning, and assuming every role in the business from coach, to barista, to receptionist, bookkeeper, marketing manager, human resource manager... you get the picture.

In saying that, at the same time I know that tearing down this wall is a GOOD thing!! It means our community has grown so much so that we need to make more space so that more of you can come and join in the fun!! To be completely honest, we imagined that it would take 3-4 years before we may have to expand, so this is a total dream come true üòç

We absolutely love our community. The positivity, the encouragement, the support, the atmosphere and the vibe is everything that we had hoped for and more. It feels like family.

So it‚Äôs time to say goodbye this wall, and hello to The Ground 2.0 üôåüèº
